sentences: Juan Bautista Plaza Alfonso (Caracas, Venezuela June 19, 1898 – 1965) was a classical composer.
He studied in Rome from 1920 and 1923 and obtained the title of professor of sagrada (sacred) composition.
After his return to Venezuela he was named Master of Chapel at Caracas Cathedral and carried out this position until the year 1948.
